## How we work

- **Read [PROJECT_STATE.md](PROJECT_STATE.md) first** — current stage, in-progress work, open questions.
- **Plan before nontrivial code.** New modules, schema changes, anything spanning components → agree the
  approach (an issue or a short design note) before writing a lot of code.
- **One unit of work = one branch = one PR.** Keep PRs small enough to review in one sitting.

## Branch & PR workflow

- Branch off `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`: `{{BRANCH_PATTERN}}` (e.g. `feat/decision-evaluator`). **No direct
  commits to `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`.**
- [Conventional Commits](docs/conventions.md) for messages.
- Open a PR; link the issue it closes. CI must be green.
- At least **{{N_REVIEWERS}}** approving review(s), and reviewers from [CODEOWNERS](CODEOWNERS) for the
  areas you touched. Resolve all review threads before merge.
- {{MERGE_STRATEGY}} (e.g. squash-merge) into `{{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`.

## Definition of Done

A change is done when: CI is green on the PR, it's approved, no unresolved comments, and — if it finished a
stage — `PROJECT_STATE.md` is updated and any decision is recorded as an ADR. See
[docs/definition-of-done.md](docs/definition-of-done.md) if present.

## Decisions

Significant, hard-to-reverse, or cross-component choices get an ADR in `docs/decisions/`. Open it as
`Status: Proposed` in your PR so the team can weigh in; it flips to `Accepted` when the PR merges. Small
cross-cutting rules go in `docs/conventions.md` instead.

